            <h2>Project Documentation</h2>
            <h3>Overview</h3>
            <p>The Trip Planner is an application that helps users find the fastest, cheapest, or most direct route between two cities based on user input. The routes are calculated using algorithms like Dijkstra for shortest path and BFS for direct routes.</p>
            
            <h3>Features</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Fastest Route: Find the route that takes the least time to travel.</li>
                <li>Cheapest Route: Calculate the route with the lowest cost.</li>
                <li>Direct Route: Find a route with the fewest stops between cities.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Technologies Used</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript</li>
                <li>Backend: Node.js, Express</li>
                <li>Java: Dijkstra's Algorithm, BFS Implementation</li>
                <li>CSV Parsing for Data Input</li>
            </ul>
